## My Experience
I used to be a local tutor teaching students younger than me, but not young enough to have them teach letters from scratch.

My *Professional Experience* Starts from
### Piston Technologies (Intern) Jan 26 - Mar 26
#### A US based Fin-Tech Startup
I interned at Piston as an Onsite Backend Developer.

Me and the team I was assigned to, worked on quarterly sprints and Agile Methodology to deliver results as fast and productive as possible.

By the time I joined, I was assigned to optimize backend and it's pre-existing functions, which later was resolved to refactoring the entire prisma stack to raw SQL. The difference in "Time To Last Bites" was phenomenal, upto ~50% faster which was obvious because of the typescript wrapper.

On top of it, I also helped mitigate critical backend vulnerabilities like SQL Injections & Cross Site Scripting.

I learned many things- technical, non-technical lessons, the unspoken rules etc from the team I was assigned in, which was far more valuable than the certificate I was handed after.
[/Box]

